Manchester United target Arturo Vidal insists he would love to play for one of the biggest clubs in the world and will sort his future when he arrives back from his holidays.

Vidal, who featured in Chile's impressive World Cup campaign, is reportedly being chased by new United boss Louis van Gaal, and the Dutchman should step up efforts when he returns from his duty at the World Cup.

